	Member	2/23/2015 5:08:40 PM	11/17/2012	10	m-groll@msn.com	Maria 	 I have a potted garden in a large condo terrace where I grow small citrus trees (4 in all) a collection of begonia plants (I belong to the Begonia Society as a Board member) various lettuce and kale for salads. I also grow all the fresh herbs for cooking. I have a small collection of Pelargoniums (I used to belong to that society). I have 2 rose bushes and a largish Plumaria (about 25yrs. old in the same large pot and doing well every year) next to it is a capricious Westeria that blooms only when I threaten to get rid of it. I am sure by now you think I am a serious mental case but I do have fun caring and understanding what the needs are of different plants. I started gardening as a small child with my mother and grandmother in Europe where I was born and where growing food was the natural thing to do. I am always seeking information and happy when I can pass it on whenever called for.I also garden in a community garden with another member of SLOLA, Lorrie Blech, she was kind to invite me to share her plot at Ocean View Farms. For several years now I am wait listed to get my own plot. Lorrie and I do best growing tomatoes in the summer. We do experiment with other vegetables and of late we have grown potatoes.	beginner		Santa Monica 	90403	415 Montana Ave 	1	000446	Groll 			Azita	3104514760		beginner	1		CA								
