	Member	1/29/2015 12:44:52 AM	01/17/2015	10	petersoncarol@yahoo.com	Carol 	 I've been gardening most of my adult life and started growing organic food for my family when my sons were little.  We lived in Long Beach, Monterey and Pacific Grove, Redondo Beach, San Diego, and back to Redondo Beach where I live at zip code 90277I used to buy seeds, but then they disappeared for awhile, so I grew things from cuttings and parts of plants and would grow from seeds that I got from avocados and other foods like potatoes (before they started spraying them to keep them from sprouting).  I started growing orchids when I was able to buy a large number of them from an estate sale and I still have some orchids.  My favorite flowers are orchids, roses, irises, and sunflowers.  The sunflowers are for the parrots that live around here.  I also bought a grevillea tree for the hummingbirds, who are my favorite birds.  I also grow organic mostly heirloom vegetables using homemade compost and some fruit trees as well as organic herbs and ginger.  I've been saving seeds for the past several years and have lots of arugula seeds	intermediate		Redondo Beach	90277	711 Diamond St 	1	000869	Peterson 	Venice		Azita			intermediate	1		CA 		4/15/2017	1		Italian Wild Arugula	01724	GRN54817SLO	
