	Member	3/31/2015 11:04:19 PM		10	alijandra1@gmail.com	Alijandra 	I live in the coastal strip of San Diego, 10B I think. More than the coastal strip, I live in what is called the banana belt in the curve where Pt Loma shelters us from the West and we overlook San Diego Bay just to our East.I was raised in Ontario, California and my father worked for Armstrong Nurseries. He had a degree in forestry and we gardened since I was about 5. My father's family moved to the Pomona Valley in the later part of the 1800s and one grandfather built Palms, in Los Angeles so we have always had great interest in native plants of all kinds. One grandmother was Pomo and taught me to forage for plants and how to use a variety of wild plants. As a result, I have some wild mountain oregano nurtured for many years if you would like some for your library. I have to do container gardening and concentrate on heritage plants. So, I also have seeds available from purple and yellow heritage tomatoes, Hopi black pinto beans, and a couple of others I don't recall at the moment.						1	000872	Mogilner	SFVVenice	paypalmembership email sent. 	Azita				1										
