	Member	6/5/2015 6:46:55 PM	04/25/2015	10	gardentechy@earthlink.net	Nadine 	I have been gardening all my life. As a kid, we grew food for our family of 6 in Van Nuys. I am a Master Gardener since completing the program in 2004. I am especially interested in heirloom plants of the world. There are many foods used from all over the world that grow well here and might have good nutritious benefits.Right now I have Cape Gooseberries grown in So. Africa that I  was introduced to by a gardener from there who now leaves here. I also have a lot of tuber plants usually grown in other countries...Oca, special gingers, edible cannas. I like to cook and explore new ingredients...It is probably easiest to email me. I am starting a garden at Los Angeles Mission College. It is easier for me to come to a meeting in the San Fernando Valley.			Van Nuys	91405	13821 Valerio St 	1	000944	Cano 	SFV	SFv	Azita	818 780			1		Ca		4/24/2015			Metki White Serpent  Cucumber	1366	CUC11011BCH	
